A '''boomerang''' is a type of [[ranged weapon]] that appears in ''[[NetHack]]''. It is made of [[wood]], and can be stacked and [[multishot]]. 

== Boomerang skill ==
{{boomerang skill table}}

Boomerangs are the only weapons to use the '''boomerang skill'''.

==Description==
When thrown, a boomerang will travel in a circular path counterclockwise from the direction thrown, hitting anything in its path: it will alternate with [[(]] as it flies to show spinning.{{refsrc|src/zap.c|3531|version=NetHack 3.6.6}} If it makes its way back to you, there is a ([[dexterity]] in 20) chance of catching the boomerang safely{{refsrc|src/zap.c|3570|version=NetHack 3.6.6}} - if this rolls fails, or the boomerang is [[cursed]] or thrown while [[fumbling]], you are hit, aborting any multishot attempts.{{refsrc|src/zap.c|3515|version=NetHack 3.6.6}}

Boomerangs will not return if their path is blocked by a wall, or if they move over a [[sink]].{{refsrc|src/zap.c|3585|version=NetHack 3.6.6}}

When used as a melee weapon rather than thrown, a boomerang has a luck-dependent chance of breaking into splinters.{{refsrc|src/uhitm.c|750|version=NetHack 3.6.6}}

{{todo|Boomerangs in 3.6.0 seem to stop whenever they pass over or hit a monster.}}

